-- England Leads Australia by 15 Runs in First Ashes Cricket Test
-- B y   B o b   B e n s c h
-- 2013-07-11T17:38:49Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2013-07-11/england-leads-australia-by-15-runs-in-first-ashes-cricket-test.html
England  leads  Australia  by 15 runs
in the opening Test of the Ashes cricket series, as record-setting Ashton Agar led the visitors on day two.  England reached 80-2 at stumps at Trent Bridge in
Nottingham, with captain Alastair Cook 37 not out and Kevin
Pietersen on 35.  Australia had taken the lead by scoring 280 in reply to
Englandâ€™s first-innings 215. Agar, who is making his Test debut,
scored 98 to set a record for most runs by a No. 11 in a Test
match. The 19-year-old also teamed with Phil Hughes, who was 81
not out, for 163 runs, the highest 10th-wicket stand in Test
history.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
